    "uses": "Clopidogrel is primarily used to prevent cardiovascular events in patients with a history of atherosclerosis, undergoing stenting, or suffering from acute coronary syndrome. It may also be used in patients with ischemic stroke or transient ischemic attack to reduce the risk of further events.\n\nAdditionally, clopidogrel is often prescribed in combination with other medications, such as aspirin, to provide enhanced protection against thrombotic complications after certain cardiovascular procedures like angioplasty or in the management of patients with coronary artery disease.",
